> style calipers, which I traded for core on the
> remanned two bleeder type that Advance said was it.
> Also, they gave me two of the same side, as any way I
> turn them, the pistons are turned differently, i.e.
> one side is up and one side is down.  I think they
> just gave me two of the same side.  The real problem
> lies in that the pads they gave me are too large to
> fit between the interior of the caliper and the rotor.
>  Yes, the pistons are in all the way, but the pad will
> not even engage the piston, as it is stopped by the
> caliper.  I contacted Advance about the problem, and
> they said that one company listed one part number for
